## 1. Purpose

This folder owns the **print-ready KFM wordmark** and its companion governance artifacts. The primary asset is `kfm-wordmark-print.pdf` — a vector PDF intended for prepress workflows (CMYK-aware press conversion, vinyl signage, dossier covers, exhibit panels, and other physical surfaces).

The README sets the rules for what lives in this folder, what each asset must be paired with (sidecar manifest, license declaration, artifact digest), and how a downstream consumer verifies authenticity before printing or embedding.

> [!NOTE]
> "Print-ready" here is the **distribution intent**, not a guarantee of conformance. Press-house conformance (PDF/X, color profile, output intent) is **NEEDS VERIFICATION** until the production export pipeline is documented and tested.

---

## 2. Authority level

| Aspect | Value |
|---|---|
| **Authority class** | `implementation-bearing` *(PROPOSED)* — the asset *is* the brand artifact for print contexts |
| **Canonical home?** | **PROPOSED** — Directory Rules §6.1 places brand assets at `docs/brand/` "*only if not in `packages/ui/`*". The alternative home cannot be ruled out from this session. |
| **Compatibility class** | n/a until an ADR closes the canonical-home question |
| **Trust-bearing?** | Yes — citation-class artifact; subject to artifact-digest discipline |

> [!WARNING]
> The `docs/brand/` ↔ `packages/ui/` ambiguity is an **ADR backlog candidate** (see §18). Do not treat this folder as canonical until the ADR is accepted; do not create a parallel sibling under `packages/ui/brand/` without an ADR, per Directory Rules §2.4(5).

