## 8. Governance diagram

A print-wordmark asset is generated outside the repo, admitted via a documented export workflow, paired with a sidecar manifest, license declaration, and digest, and then either embedded in published artifacts or distributed standalone. The Mermaid diagram below sketches the **PROPOSED** governed flow.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Vector source<br/>design tool<br/>EXTERNAL] -->|deterministic export| B[kfm-wordmark-print.pdf]
    B --> C[Compute spec_hash<br/>jcs:sha256]
    B --> D[Compute artifact_digest<br/>sha256 of linearized PDF]
    C --> E[Sidecar manifest<br/>kfm-wordmark-print.pdf.sidecar.json]
    D --> E
    F[License declaration<br/>kfm-wordmark-print.license.md] --> E
    E --> G{Validation gate}
    G -->|pass| H[Eligible for embed / distribution]
    G -->|fail| I[QUARANTINE — fix and re-export]
    H --> J[Embedded in C13 PDF builds]
    H --> K[Distributed standalone to press]
    style I fill:#fbb,stroke:#933
    style H fill:#bfb,stroke:#393
```

> [!NOTE]
> Diagram is **PROPOSED**. It mirrors Directory Rules §8 (compatibility/canonical placement) and C13-01 / C13-04 (toolchain pinning, ARTIFACT_DIGEST). The validation gate is conceptual; the actual validator and its policy bundle are **NEEDS VERIFICATION**.

