## 9. Specifications

The fields below define the **expected** technical profile of `kfm-wordmark-print.pdf`. Concrete values are **PROPOSED placeholders** pending an authoritative export specification.

| Property | Expected value | Status |
|---|---|---|
| Page geometry | Single page, tight crop to wordmark bounds | PROPOSED |
| Color space | CMYK with embedded output intent *(e.g. `Coated GRACoL 2013`)* | PROPOSED |
| PDF conformance | PDF/X-4 (preferred for press) or PDF/A-2u (preferred for archive) | PROPOSED |
| Font embedding | All fonts embedded (subset acceptable) | PROPOSED — aligns with C13-02 |
| Transparency | Flattened to vector + spot/CMYK; no live transparency under PDF/X-4 | PROPOSED |
| Bleed / trim | Not applicable for a wordmark-only asset; if framed, include 3 mm bleed | PROPOSED |
| Minimum reproduction size | TBD (typical wordmark floor: 25 mm wide) | PROPOSED |
| Clear space | TBD (typically ≥ x-height of the wordmark on all sides) | PROPOSED |
| Linearization | qpdf-linearized for streamable distribution | PROPOSED — aligns with C13-04 |
| Tagged structure | Tagged for PDF/UA where the asset is embedded in accessible documents | PROPOSED — aligns with C13-03 |
| Identity hashes | `spec_hash = jcs:sha256:<hex>`; `artifact_digest = sha256:<hex>` over linearized bytes | PROPOSED — aligns with C1-02 / C13-04 |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The values above are **PROPOSED**. Substitute concrete values only when a brand steward signs off on the export specification and an export manifest is committed alongside the asset.

