## 13. Validation

Validation checks that should run before a wordmark is treated as **eligible for embed / distribution**. All gates are **PROPOSED** and fail-closed.

| Gate | Check | Pass criterion | Fail mode |
|---|---|---|---|
| **V1 Presence** | All required files present (PDF + sidecar + license) | All three exist | `DENY` |
| **V2 Spec hash** | Recompute `spec_hash` over the sidecar's normalized spec | Matches recorded hash | `DENY` (drift) |
| **V3 Artifact digest** | Recompute SHA-256 over linearized PDF | Matches sidecar value | `DENY` (tampering / drift) |
| **V4 Font embed** | All fonts embedded in the PDF | No `Not embedded` references | `DENY` |
| **V5 Color profile** | Output intent present and matches sidecar | Match | `ABSTAIN` if absent; `DENY` on mismatch |
| **V6 PDF conformance** | veraPDF or equivalent reports the conformance level recorded in sidecar | Pass | `DENY` |
| **V7 License visible** | `license.md` declares license, attribution, permitted use | Present and non-empty | `DENY` (per ML-F-002 / ML-F-004) |
| **V8 Accessibility** | Tagged structure / PDF/UA where the asset is embedded in accessible builds | Pass | `ABSTAIN` for standalone print use; `DENY` for accessible-build embed |

> [!WARNING]
> Validators V1 – V8 are **PROPOSED**. None are confirmed to exist in the repo. Do not treat this table as evidence of running CI checks.

