## 16. FAQ

**Q. Why is a single PDF asset governed like a release artifact?**

A wordmark PDF cited from a published dossier is **citation-class**. If the file silently changes, every downstream receipt that pointed at it now points at moving content. Treating the wordmark as a release artifact — with a `spec_hash`, an `artifact_digest`, and a sidecar manifest — preserves the citation chain. *(Doctrine: C13-04 ARTIFACT_DIGEST as Citation Anchor.)*

**Q. Should the wordmark live in `docs/brand/` or in `packages/ui/`?**

Directory Rules explicitly leaves this open: "*styles guides, logo, voice — only if not in `packages/ui/`*". This README assumes `docs/brand/` provisionally. An ADR is needed to close the question. **PROPOSED.**

**Q. PDF/X-4 or PDF/A-2u?**

PDF/X-4 is the conventional print-distribution conformance target. PDF/A-2u is the project's PDF archival/linearization target under C13. Both can coexist (an asset can be PDF/X-4 and still pass PDF/A-2u checks for archival), but the export workflow must declare which conformance the file claims. **PROPOSED — pending the brand-export spec.**

**Q. What happens when the wordmark changes?**

The rotation is a release event. The new file has a new `artifact_digest`. Every downstream document that embedded the prior wordmark now references a stale digest; correction notices and re-issued builds may be required for already-published artifacts.

