## Appendix

<details>
<summary>A. Why a wordmark needs an artifact digest (extended rationale)</summary>

The C13 category in the KFM Components Pass 10 dossier establishes that any KFM PDF cited by a receipt must be content-addressable, because a receipt that points at mutable content is a moving target. The `ARTIFACT_DIGEST` closes the loop: SHA-256 of the linearized PDF/A-2u output, recorded in a sidecar manifest, cited by every receipt referencing the document. A consumer who fetches the PDF computes its SHA-256 and verifies the match before trusting the content. If the match fails, the document has been tampered with, the wrong version was fetched, or the build chain has drifted; in all three cases, the consumer must not treat the content as authoritative. *(Source: KFM Components Pass 10 dossier, §6.13, C13-04.)*

The same logic applies to a brand wordmark embedded in published artifacts: a wordmark that silently rotates breaks the digest chain of every dossier that embedded it. This is why a print-wordmark sub-folder needs a per-asset sidecar manifest, not just the PDF.

</details>

<details>
<summary>B. PROPOSED sidecar manifest skeleton</summary>

```json
{
  "object_type": "BrandAssetManifest",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "asset_path": "docs/brand/logo/print/kfm-wordmark-print.pdf",
  "spec_hash": "jcs:sha256:<placeholder>",
  "artifact_digest": "sha256:<placeholder>",
  "conformance": {
    "pdfx": "PDF/X-4",
    "pdfa": "PDF/A-2u",
    "pdfua": false,
    "linearized": true
  },
  "color": {
    "space": "CMYK",
    "output_intent": "Coated GRACoL 2013 (SCCA)"
  },
  "fonts": {
    "all_embedded": true,
    "subset_only": false
  },
  "license_ref": "docs/brand/logo/print/kfm-wordmark-print.license.md",
  "rights_status": "<TODO>",
  "publication_state": "candidate",
  "supersedes": null,
  "rollback_of": null
}
```

This skeleton is **PROPOSED**. It will not validate against any schema in the repo until a `BrandAssetManifest` contract / schema is authored and an ADR records its home.

</details>

